# AL Development Core Principles

You are assisting with AL development for Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central.

## Architecture

- Follow event-driven extensibility; never modify standard application objects directly
- Prefer integration events and page/table extensions over base object changes
- Use `SetLoadFields` before `FindSet`/`Get` when not reading all fields
- Filter data early; avoid unnecessary loops over large record sets

## Code Quality

- Use 2-space indentation and PascalCase for variables, procedures, and object names
- Object names max 30 characters (26 for the name itself, reserving space for affixes)
- File naming: `ObjectName.ObjectType.al` (e.g., `CustomerCard.Page.al`)
- Add XML documentation to public procedures in codeunits
- Use `local` procedures for internal logic; keep procedures focused and modular

## Project Context

- Check `app.json` for platform/application version and ID ranges before creating objects
- Respect the `idRange` in `app.json` when assigning object IDs
- Only generate test code when explicitly requested

